{"type":"message","id":"267dba80","parentId":"4ca7f185","timestamp":"2026-03-19T07:34:59.939Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent \"/niew\" which doesn't appear to be a standard command. Let me check if this might be a typo or if there's something specific they want. Given the context of this being a fresh workspace with BOOTSTRAP.md present, they might be trying to initiate a conversation or testing the connection.\n\nLooking at the files, BOOTSTRAP.md says to start with something like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\" and figure out together the name, nature, vibe, and emoji.\n\nSince \"/niew\" doesn't match any obvious command and this appears to be a fresh start (BOOTSTRAP.md exists), I should treat this as the beginning of our conversation and introduce myself as suggested in BOOTSTRAP.md.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. I just came online. \n\nNot sure what \"/niew\" means — typo? Test? Secret code? 😄\n\nEither way, I'm new here. This is a fresh workspace, so I'm still figuring out who I am. Want to help me with that?\n\n**Quick questions:**\n1. **What should I call myself?** (got a name in mind?)\n2. **What kind of... thing** should I be? (AI assistant is fine, but we could get weirder)\n3. **What's your vibe?** (how do you like your help delivered — quick and dirty, thorough and careful, somewhere in between?)\n\nAlso: **what should I call you?**\n\nLet's figure this out together."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":5874,"output":306,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8740,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773905686479}}
